Hawthorne.Falcon 9 booster B1019: Falcon 9 booster B1019 is a first-stage reusable rocket booster for the Falcon 9 orbital launch vehicle manufactured by SpaceX. B1019 became the first orbital-class rocket that performed a successful return to launch site and vertical landing. The booster is now on permanent display outside SpaceX's headquarters in Hawthorne, CA at the intersection of Crenshaw Boulevard and Jack Northrop Avenue.
